The paper deals with interactive object selection using deep learning techniques, which is a problem commonly studied in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) communities. The use of deep learning models to reduce user interactions also suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of graph cut optimization, which is a common technique in computer graphics (cs.GR) for image segmentation. Finally, the evaluation of the algorithm on different datasets suggests a focus on multimedia (cs.MM) applications.
